			<h3>Professors Wang, Menekse, and Litman Collaborate with Grad Students on CourseMIRROR Project</h3>
			<img src="/img/uploads/news/962-rsz_coursemirror.png" alt="" />			<p id="short962" class="multiline">
				<b>Professors Wang, Menekse, and Litman are collaborating with grad students on an exciting new project, CourseMIRROR! </b>CourseMIRROR improves student-instructor interactions in large-classrooms and Massive Open Online Courses (MOOCs) via mobile interfaces and natural language processing. CourseMIRROR facilitates learning at scale by enabling students to reflect in-situ via mobile devices. It also helps instructors to capture the gist of reflections effectively via natural language processing. CourseMIRROR is free and supports major mobile platforms and PCs. Please visit <a href= "http://www.coursemirror.com">http://www.coursemirror.com</a> for more details.<a href="/pages/%23" class="moreLink" id="long962" data-id="962"></a>			</p>
			<p id="long962" class="long">
				<b>Professors Wang, Menekse, and Litman are collaborating with grad students on an exciting new project, CourseMIRROR! </b>CourseMIRROR improves student-instructor interactions in large-classrooms and Massive Open Online Courses (MOOCs) via mobile interfaces and natural language processing. CourseMIRROR facilitates learning at scale by enabling students to reflect in-situ via mobile devices. It also helps instructors to capture the gist of reflections effectively via natural language processing. CourseMIRROR is free and supports major mobile platforms and PCs. Please visit <a href= "http://www.coursemirror.com">http://www.coursemirror.com</a> for more details.			</p>
		</li>
